# Copy to `.env.development.local` (gitignored) to override Vite dev settings on your machine.
#
# Host Vite + Django on a non-default port (e.g. 8000 taken by another app):
# API_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8002
#
# Default when unset: http://127.0.0.1:8000 (see vite.config.ts)
# vite.config.ts uses Vite loadEnv() so variables here (and in `.env`) apply to `npm run dev`.
